<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Berlese (1883a) created the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Nassariidae" genus="Tritia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Tritia</taxonomicName>
, with 
<taxonomicName authority="Koch, 1835" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="1835" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Hoplophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decumana">Hoplophora decumana C. L. Koch</taxonomicName>
as type; he used the generic name later on for species of the families 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Oribotritiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Oribotritiidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Euphthiracaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Euphthiracaridae</taxonomicName>
. Michael (1898) placed 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Nassariidae" genus="Tritia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Tritia</taxonomicName>
in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Phthiracarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Phthiracarus</taxonomicName>
Perty, and Berlese adopted this opinion between 1904 and 1913, when he contributed species of the above-mentioned two families to 
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1904" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1904" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Phtiracarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Phtiracarus</taxonomicName>
. Berlese (1913a) published a diagnosis of &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1904" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1904" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Phtiracarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Phtiracarus</taxonomicName>
&quot; and designated 
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1904" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1904" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Phtiracarus" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="berlesei">P. berlesei</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Oribotritiidae" genus="Oribotritia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decumana">Oribotritia decumana</taxonomicName>
) as type of the genus, although 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Phthiracarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Phthiracarus</taxonomicName>
is monotypical (type: 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Phthiracarus" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contractilis">P. contractilis</taxonomicName>
). In his 1916 and 1923 papers Berlese returned, however, to the use of 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Nassariidae" genus="Tritia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Tritia</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Jacot (1924) discovered that 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Nassariidae" genus="Tritia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Tritia</taxonomicName>
is preoccupied. For this reason he created the new name 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Oribotritiidae" genus="Oribotritia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Oribotritia</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Koch, 1835" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="1835" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Hoplophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decumana">Hoplophora decumana</taxonomicName>
is of course also the type of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Oribotritiidae" genus="Oribotritia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Oribotritia</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Three species of the genus are dealt with in Berlese's papers.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
